Hi all!

Does someone know some stuff about the AHI library
interface ?

My question:
When I playback sound data it has a slightly crackling
noise in it. The higher frequencies are more affected then the
lower. I found out that is has something to do with
the soundfunc hook I am using for doublebuffering.
How much time I am allowed to spend in the soudnfunc hook ?
I do mixing some audiostreams to fill the next (short) buffer.

Seems like I am spending more time than one sample (sampleframe!)
needs for playback and the AHI system is blocked and repeats 
this sample (thats why lower noises are not much affected,
as neighboured samples are almost equal).

This would mean the time to spend in the soudnfunc hook is limited
to the duration of one sample, e.g. 1/44100 sec if you playback
at 44100 Hz.

Any ideas ?

Anyone did a bit more than setting up the loop within the soundfunc ?

Ciao,

Thilo


