Hi,

> I have checked it with Snoopdos:
> My program opens locale.libary before KS checking!
> Is there any solution for checking KS?

The reason for this is that all libraries are initialised at the start of your program. In 
most (all?) cases, this will include opening any OS libraries that are required.

However, this should not matter. If they library cannot be opened, it will not be. You then 
check for the version of the OS and quit if it is too old. The library will be closed on 
program exit (if it was opened).

I really do not see why this is a problem.

